If $$\gamma_0\colon [0,L] \to \R^2$$ is arc length parametrized and $$\gamma$$ is a variation of $$\gamma_0,$$ then
$$
\dot L \coloneqq
\fracderiv{}{t}\biggr|_{t=0} L(\gamma_t) =
  \lang \dot\gamma,T \rang\bigr|_0^L +
  \int_0^L \kappa \lang \dot\gamma,N \rang \,\d s.
$$

